Zion National Park is located in southwestern Utah. The park is at the confluence of the Colorado Plateau, the Great Basin, and the Mojave desert, giving it a unique variety of geology and life zones. The centerpoint of the park is Zion Canyon, a colorful sandstone canyon which is 15 miles long and up to 2,600 feet deep.